Biography

CAREER HIGHLIGHTS (THROUGH 2023-24 SEASON)

Career Record: 2-10

AS A SENIOR (2023-24): Made four countable appearances in her senior season, going 1-3 on the year...Twice paired with Karmin Brown in the #4 spot, dropping both contests...Split a pair of matches in the #5 spot playing with Paola Peralta...Often occupied the Gaels exhibition #6 spot alongside Clarissa Klein.

AS A JUNIOR (2022-23): Appeared in eight matches during her first season in Moraga, with all eight of those appearances coming in the fifth spot...picked up her first collegiate win during the Outrigger Duke Classic in Hawaii, beating Stephen F. Austin...subbed into the twos spot againt #9 Cal with Genevieve Bane on April 21.

PRIOR TO SAINT MARY'S: Transfers to Saint Mary's after spending one season at MiraCosta College...racked up 258 digs while also posting 106 kills for the Spartans as a freshman, helping her land PCAC Second Team All-Conference honors in 2021...in high school, Martinez was named All-Metro 4A First Team and All-State in 2019, while earning District 5AAAA First Team honors...also a standout in the classroom, taking home two All-District Academic awards in 2018 and 2019.

Favorite volleyball memory: Winning the New Mexico State Championship my senior year.

Favorite holiday: Christmas

What do you love most about Saint Mary’s: I love how friendly everyone is and getting to meet and talk to so many new people.

Favorite thing about SMC Volleyball: I love that the team is so welcoming. It truly feels like a family away from home.

Favorite food or meal: steak

Top-3 favorite songs: in no particular order…Magic by Coldplay, Tulsa Texas by Easton Corbin, Careless Whisper by George Michael

Favorite Movie: Mama Mia

Personal Hobbies: video games

One thing everyone should do in their lifetime: Go see the Albuquerque International Balloon Fiesta

Describe yourself in one word: Humorous
